---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
const jsonLD = { '@context': 'https://schema.org', '@type': 'WebPage', name: 'Privacy Policy' };
const updated = '2026-07-02';
---

<BaseLayout title="Privacy Policy" description="How VisaLang handles visitor data, cookies, and analytics." jsonLD={jsonLD} noindex={true}>
  <main class="page-shell">
    <article class="guide-article narrow-page">
        <p class="eyebrow">Legal</p>
        <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
        <p class="guide-summary">Last updated: {updated}</p>

        <h2>Overview</h2>
        <p>VisaLang (flowlight.me) is a static informational website. We do not require you to create an account, and we do not collect sensitive personal data such as passport numbers, immigration documents, or payment details.</p>

        <h2>Information we collect</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Analytics data:</strong> aggregate, privacy-friendly metrics such as page views, country, and referrer, collected via Plausible Analytics. We do not use cross-site tracking cookies.</li>
          <li><strong>Direct contact:</strong> if you email us, your email provider and ours process the address, message, and any information you choose to include.</li>
          <li><strong>Server logs:</strong> standard web server logs (IP address, user agent, timestamp) retained for security and debugging purposes.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Please do not send sensitive case documents</h2>
        <p>Do not send passport scans, visa files, certificate copies, booking codes, or payment records through a public contact channel. VisaLang does not need them to assess a correction and cannot verify an individual application or certificate.</p>

        <h2>How we use information</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>To understand which guides and routes are most useful.</li>
          <li>To respond to corrections, questions, product-update requests, or partnership inquiries that you send directly.</li>
          <li>To maintain site security and prevent abuse.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Cookies</h2>
        <p>VisaLang uses minimal cookies. See our <a href="/cookie-policy/">Cookie Policy</a> for details. We do not sell data to advertisers.</p>

        <h2>Third-party links</h2>
        <p>Our guides link to official exam providers and government authorities. Once you leave flowlight.me, their privacy policies apply. We are not responsible for practices on external sites.</p>

        <h2>Advertising</h2>
        <p>If we add display advertising in the future, we will update this policy and clearly label ads. We will not place ads inside official-source sections, forms, or navigation.</p>

        <h2>Your rights</h2>
        <p>If you contacted us and want your message or email address removed where applicable, contact <a href="/contact/">us</a>. Residents of the EU, UK, and California may have additional rights under GDPR or CCPA.</p>

        <h2>Children</h2>
        <p>VisaLang is not directed at children under 16 and we do not knowingly collect their data.</p>

        <h2>Changes</h2>
        <p>We may update this policy. The Last Updated date above reflects the most recent revision. For a particular service such as analytics, an email form, or an external provider, the current service notice controls where applicable.</p>

        <h2>Contact</h2>
        <p>Questions about privacy? See our <a href="/contact/">contact page</a>.</p>

        <p class="compliance-line">This privacy policy is provided for informational purposes and does not constitute legal advice.</p>
        <p class="last-updated">Last updated: {updated}</p>
    </article>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>
